                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004"/><desc>Tewodros on Horseback with caption <q>“Tewodros.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004"/><desc>David on the throne with caption <q>“Saint David.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#113v" facs="116"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> in full color with pencil drawing of <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/> above and defeated foe below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#114r" facs="116"/><desc> Man (<ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref>?) with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/> in full color with braided <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> in pencil</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #33r #65r" facs="003 035 067"/> (ornate colored ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#97r" facs="099"/> (ornate ḥaräg in black ink);
                    <locus target="#110v" facs="113"/> (ḥaräg in black ink);
                    <locus target="#12r #18r #26v #32v #37v #45r #54r #61r #64v #83v #86r #96v #108r" facs="014 020 029 035 040 047 056 063 067 086 088 099 110"/> (multiple full stops between alternating black and red dotted lines);
                    <locus target="#91r #109v" facs="093 112"/> (alternating black and red dotted line);
                    <locus target="#108r #109r #113r" facs="110 111 115"/> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002"> f. iv(erso), upper</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1451GadlaG">Gadla Gabra Manfas Qǝddus (general record)</title>. Marrassini, Vita Omelia Miracoli del Santo Gabra Manfas Qeddus
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002"> f. iv(erso), lower</locus>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                      two <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer (general record)</title>s against cough.
                      Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዙሐል ፯ ወአረሚ ሕርናኤል አቶ በቶን ንበዋቶን በዝንቱ አስማቲከ ከመ ኢይፃዕ ትፋት እምላዕከ ገብርከ<gap reason="omitted"/> </foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#108v #113r" facs="111 115"/>
                    <desc>
                      On the obligation of the clergy to teach the faithful, in Amharic.
                      Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="am">በስመ አብ ወወልድ<gap reason="omitted"/> ይህን ካህናት ብቻ ይስሙት ሕገ እግዚአብሔር የማያስተምር የማይመክር ካህን ቢገኝ ይሻር አለ ሰው ባይሽረው እግዚአብሔር ከሻረው ምን ክህነት አለው<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #ivv(erso) #114v" facs="001 002 003 005 117"/>
                    <desc>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#108r" facs="110"/>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of ownership, owner’s name erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#Back Cover" facs="140"/>
                    <desc>
                    The back cover has a recessed niche in which there was probably a mirror at one time
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Binding is intact and appears to be rebound
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Vellum is discolored but generally in good condition
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–4, 6–8, and 10–12
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#27r #30v #31r #32v" facs="029 033 033 035"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#5r #8v #22v #24r" facs="007 011 025 026"/>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#44r #47v #84v" facs="046 050 087"/>
                    <desc>
                    12.	The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of text above the end of the line
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
